CatDescriptText: Cutline of image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, May 4, 1957, pg. A9 reads: "Peabody Clean-Up Speakers - The students at Peabody High School began the annual city-wide clean-up, paint-up, plant-up campaign with two 15-minute assemblies and a Dress-up Day. The speakers at the assemblies were, left to right, seated: Mike Kay, Wayne Holt and vice principal, Mr. Mong.  Standing is Connie Roseman. - Harris Photo."
TitMainTitle: Connie Roseman, standing at microphone, with from left: Mike Kay, Wayne Holt, and Mr. Mong, seated on stage during assembly in Peabody High School
